Summaries for HSD17B2 Gene

GeneCards Summary for HSD17B2 Gene

HSD17B2 (Hydroxysteroid (17-Beta) Dehydrogenase 2) is a Protein Coding gene. Diseases associated with HSD17B2 include progesterone resistance and endometriosis of ovary. Among its related pathways are Metabolism and Ovarian steroidogenesis. GO annotations related to this gene include oxidoreductase activity and testosterone dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity. An important paralog of this gene is HSD11B2.

UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot for HSD17B2 Gene

  • DHB2_HUMAN,P37059

  • Capable of catalyzing the interconversion of testosterone and androstenedione, as well as estradiol and estrone. Also has 20-alpha-HSD activity. Uses NADH while EDH17B3 uses NADPH.

17-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase,type II,microsomal,NAD dependent,converting estrogens and androgens,playing an essential role in the formation of active intracellular sex steroids

  • DHB2_HUMAN,P37059
UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot CatalyticActivity:
17-beta-estradiol + NAD(P)(+) = estrone + NAD(P)H.
  • DHB2_HUMAN,P37059
UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot CatalyticActivity:
Testosterone + NAD(+) = androstenedione + NADH.
  • DHB2_HUMAN,P37059
UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot Function:
Capable of catalyzing the interconversion of testosterone and androstenedione, as well as estradiol and estrone. Also has 20-alpha-HSD activity. Uses NADH while EDH17B3 uses NADPH.
